FBIS4-29986 "dreas121_j_94007" FBIS-EAS-94-121 Daily Report 22 Jun 1994 Indonesia Further Reportage on Government Media Ban Further Reportage on Government Media Ban Openness Said Not Affected BK2206134294 Jakarta ANTARA in English 1214 GMT 22 Jun 94 BK2206134294 Jakarta ANTARA English BFN [Text] Jakarta, Jun 22 (OANA/ANTARA) -- State/Minister Secretary Murdiono stressed here Wednesday that the government will hold on to its policy of openness including the media although it revoked on Tuesday publishing licences of three major Jakarta weeklies. "The press community would have no problems if they only know how to abide by the country's journalism code of ethics (KEJ) and other existing regulations. "Follow the KEJ and there would be no problems," Murdiono said.
